      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "NISTIRITH (6) got the job done over 1100m last time out at this track in a strong maiden victory. She's shown plenty of talent throughout her career thus far and now gets out to 1200m for the first time. Too good as an odds-on pop last time out and she can go on with the job now. STYLIN' (7) wasn't disgraced when beaten 3.8L on the Scarpside at Pinjarra most recently. Gets onto her home deck today and the drop back to 1200m may be the key. Fiore remains in the saddle and with a touch of luck from the draw, she'll be hard to hold out. JAYASHREE (3) resumes here without a trial but rates highly on the form she produced last time out. May get back from the draw, but if she can pick up from where she left off last campaign, she'll be in the mix. GUARD THE MULLAH (2) led and missed last time out over further here 9 days ago. Back in trip and the claim of Cheung help. COULDABEENAHANDBAG (4) not out of this on her recent effort.",
